      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HELLO NEMO (2) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish a neck away in second (23.13) at this track in a Grade 5 over 401m. Yet to miss the placings in four runs from this box, including two wins. Sure to be about the mark. GO GO SPIRIT (4) has a strong record here with five wins and five placings from 12 starts. Was out of placings last time (30.69) at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5, finishing fourth and beaten 13 lengths. Looks a key chance on best figures. TAP OUT RUSTY (7) has missed the placings at his last couple but was in the money three back when third (30.38) at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5. Well placed here and can atone this time. SUNSHINE LILY (3) can play a role in the finish without surprising.",
